#### Loading Aspects at Runtime

We can now create a service to load aspects at runtime.

```java
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;

@Service
public class AspectService {

    private final AspectRegistry aspectRegistry;

    public AspectService(AspectRegistry aspectRegistry) {
        this.aspectRegistry = aspectRegistry;
    }

    public void loadAspect(String aspectClassName) {
        try {
            aspectRegistry.registerAspect(aspectClassName);
        } catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    public void unloadAspect(String aspectClassName) {
        aspectRegistry.unregisterAspect(aspectClassName);
    }
}
```

